                            <comment id="13914374" author="01sas" created="Thu, 27 Feb 2014 10:51:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am not able to reproduce this bug in test, but it can be very easily reproduced on Wicket examples. For this you will need to perform the following steps:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;go to org.apache.wicket.examples.stateless.StatelessApplication class and add the following line to init method:
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;getPageSettings().setRecreateMountedPagesAfterExpiry(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;). 
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Start example application&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;go &lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:8080/stateless/foo&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://localhost:8080/stateless/foo&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Submit form&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13914379" author="01sas" created="Thu, 27 Feb 2014 11:02:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Possible reason of this bug is in invalid logic in Component#urlFor(Behavior,RequestListenerInterface, PageParameters) and Component#urlFor(RequestListenerInterface, PageParameters) methods. Both of this methods have the following lines of code:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (getApplication().getPageSettings().getRecreateMountedPagesAfterExpiry() &amp;amp;&amp;amp;
       ((page.isBookmarkable() &amp;amp;&amp;amp; page.wasCreatedBookmarkable()) || page.isPageStateless()))
{
    handler = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; BookmarkableListenerInterfaceRequestHandler(provider, listener, id);
}
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt;
{
    handler = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; ListenerInterfaceRequestHandler(provider, listener, id);
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;From my understanding something wrong with boolean expression in if statement. Condition page.isPageStateless() should be checked regardless of getRecreateMountedPagesAfterExpiry status. I think that this if statement should be changed to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (page.isPageStateless() || (getApplication().getPageSettings().getRecreateMountedPagesAfterExpiry() &amp;amp;&amp;amp;
        page.isBookmarkable() &amp;amp;&amp;amp; page.wasCreatedBookmarkable()))
...
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13914486" author="svenmeier" created="Thu, 27 Feb 2014 13:22:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, an &apos;or&apos; (||) makes more sense - no failing tests with the proposed change.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13914672" author="svenmeier" created="Thu, 27 Feb 2014 15:51:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Changed the condition as proposed: page#isStateless() is sufficient to use a&lt;br/&gt;
BookmarkableListenerInterfaceRequestHandler&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
